<p>
	Experience the unforgettable sunset boat tour on Lake Kivu, complete with captivating music, breathtaking scenery, and your favorite drinks. Marvel at the beauty of the lake's shores, islands, and the surrounding Rift Valley, adorned with the majestic Congo Nile mountain range. Encounter the serenity of the moment with birds chirping in the bushes and the chance to take a refreshing swim. Indulge in sundowner drinks and snacks on a tranquil island, perhaps even witnessing singing fishermen in dugout canoes as they embark on a night of fishing.
	<br>
	Embark on a guided boat tour to explore islands like Nyamunini, affectionately called Napoleon Island for its distinctive shape, offering stunning views of Lake Kivu and housing colonies of fruit bats. Continue your journey to Kinunu coffee washing station, where you'll delve into the intricate process of Rwanda's renowned coffee production. Learn firsthand from farmers and an agronomist about everything from cultivation practices to harvesting and roasting. Wrap up the tour with a refreshing break on the beach, perhaps even spotting cows taking a dip in the lake before heading back to Kibuye.
	
	
	  
</p>
